snippet.textDisplay: One caveat, if you live in California and have a family with children that were accepted into a UC, you can have all tuition waived if the family income is below $80,000 a year through the UC blue and gold program. In that case, it makes sense that you should consider declining a raise because exceeding the $80,000/yr threshold means you're entirely responsible to pay the full tuition amount of $13,509/yr. Assuming one child going into college, it makes sense to decline the raise unless it exceeds $25,000/yr until your children have graduated. Another option is to get a divorce to lower the family income amount to qualify for the program.
